# Solution: cpp_system_security_expert_064_architectural_understanding_expert_01

## Architectural Bottleneck Analysis in FortiLedger360 Security Suite

---

## Key Files Identified

| File Path | Description |
|-----------|-------------|
| `/app/project/api/v1/openapi.yaml` | OpenAPI specification defining the `/tenants/{tenantId}/scans` endpoint for initiating security scans |
| `/app/project/src/services/api_gateway/routes.cpp` | API Gateway route handlers; entry point for `POST /v1/security/scan` requests |
| `/app/project/src/services/api_gateway/server.cpp` | gRPC server implementation with Chain-of-Responsibility validation pipeline |
| `/app/project/src/lib/orchestration/command_handler.cpp` | Command handler that dispatches commands to appropriate executors via Strategy pattern |
| `/app/project/src/lib/orchestration/command_handler.h` | Command handler interface with middleware pipeline and executor registration |
| `/app/project/src/lib/domain/commands/scan_command.h` | ScanCommand domain object that encapsulates scan request intent and publishes to EventBus |
| `/app/project/src/lib/domain/strategies/payg_scan_strategy.h` | Pay-As-You-Go strategy with its own priority queue and worker pool |
| `/app/project/src/lib/domain/strategies/continuous_scan_strategy.h` | Continuous scan strategy with background worker thread for scheduled scans |
| `/app/project/src/lib/domain/strategies/isecurity_strategy.h` | Strategy interface defining the contract for security scan strategies |
| `/app/project/src/services/scanner_svc/scanner_engine.cpp` | **CRITICAL**: Core scanner engine with **single FIFO `BlockingQueue`** and worker thread pool |
| `/app/project/src/services/scanner_svc/scanner_engine.h` | Scanner engine header defining the work queue and scheduling mechanisms |
| `/app/project/src/services/scanner_svc/service_impl.cpp` | Scanner service gRPC implementation that enqueues work to the engine |
| `/app/project/cmd/scanner_svc/main.cpp` | Scanner service bootstrap with shared worker pool configuration |
| `/app/project/src/lib/infrastructure/event_bus/event_publisher.cpp` | Event publisher with FIFO queue for async event publishing |
| `/app/project/src/lib/infrastructure/event_bus/event_consumer.cpp` | Kafka-based event consumer that dispatches to domain handlers |
| `/app/project/docs/architecture/event_flows.md` | Event flow documentation showing command → event → service flow |
| `/app/project/docs/architecture/adr/002-event-driven-architecture.md` | ADR documenting the Event-Driven Architecture decisions |
| `/app/project/docs/architecture/adr/003-grpc-and-service-mesh.md` | ADR documenting gRPC and Istio service mesh decisions |

---

## Code Evidence

### 1. API Gateway Entry Point - Scan Request Initiation

```cpp
// File: /app/project/src/services/api_gateway/routes.cpp
// Lines: 209-239

/**
 * POST /v1/security/scan
 */
void initiateScan(const Http::Request& req,
                  Http::ResponseWriter resp,
                  const std::string& corrId)
{
    const auto tenantId = ensureAuthenticated(req);

    rateLimiter_.acquireToken(tenantId, "security.scan");

    json payload = parseJson(req);
    validators::RequestValidator::validateScanRequest(payload);

    auto dispatchResult = bus_->publish("InitiateSecurityScan", {
        { "correlationId", corrId },
        { "tenantId",      tenantId },
        { "scanDepth",     payload.at("scanDepth") },
        { "targets",       payload.at("targets") }
    });

    if (!dispatchResult) {
        throw errors::HttpError(Http::Code::Service_Unavailable,
                                "Unable to queue security scan at this time");
    }

    resp.send(Http::Code::Accepted, json{
        { "message", "Security scan queued" },
        { "correlationId", corrId }
    }.dump());
}
```

### 2. Command Handler Orchestration Layer

```cpp
// File: /app/project/src/lib/orchestration/command_handler.cpp
// Lines: 178-217

class CommandHandler final
{
public:
    explicit CommandHandler(std::shared_ptr<CommandRegistry> registry)
        : registry_{ std::move(registry) }
    {
        if (!registry_) { throw std::invalid_argument("registry is nullptr"); }
    }

    // Synchronous (blocking) processing
    void handle(const CommandContext& ctx, const Command& cmd)
    {
        notify_start(ctx, cmd);
        try
        {
            run_validation(ctx, cmd);
            run_execution(ctx, cmd);
            notify_success(ctx, cmd);
        }
        catch (const std::exception& ex)
        {
            notify_error(ctx, cmd, ex);
            throw;      // Re-propagate to upstream orchestrator
        }
    }

    // Asynchronous (detached) processing — returns a future
    std::future<void> dispatch_async(CommandContext ctx, Command cmd)
    {
        return std::async(std::launch::async,
                          [self = shared_from_this(), ctx = std::move(ctx), cmd = std::move(cmd)]() {
                              self->handle(ctx, cmd);
                          });
    }
```

### 3. **CRITICAL BOTTLENECK**: Scanner Engine with Single FIFO Queue

```cpp
// File: /app/project/src/services/scanner_svc/scanner_engine.cpp
// Lines: 200-241

// ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
// Thread-safe Queue (SIMPLE FIFO - NO PRIORITY)
// ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
template <typename T>
class BlockingQueue
{
public:
    explicit BlockingQueue(std::size_t max) : capacity_(max) {}

    void push(T item)
    {
        std::unique_lock lk(mu_);
        cvFull_.wait(lk, [&] { return queue_.size() < capacity_; });
        queue_.push(std::move(item));  // FIFO: items processed in arrival order
        cvEmpty_.notify_one();
    }

    bool pop(T &out)
    {
        std::unique_lock lk(mu_);
        cvEmpty_.wait(lk, [&] { return !queue_.empty() || terminated_; });
        if (queue_.empty()) return false; // terminated
        out = std::move(queue_.front());
        queue_.pop();
        cvFull_.notify_one();
        return true;
    }

    // ...
private:
    std::size_t                capacity_;
    std::queue<T>              queue_;  // std::queue = FIFO, NO PRIORITY
    std::mutex                 mu_;
    std::condition_variable    cvFull_, cvEmpty_;
    bool                       terminated_ {false};
};
```

### 4. Scanner Engine Worker Pool - Shared Across All Tenants

```cpp
// File: /app/project/src/services/scanner_svc/scanner_engine.cpp
// Lines: 246-274

class ScannerEngine
{
public:
    explicit ScannerEngine(std::size_t workerCount = std::thread::hardware_concurrency())
        : queue_(1024), log_(), shuttingDown_(false)  // Single queue with fixed capacity
    {
        workerCount = std::max<std::size_t>(1, workerCount);
        log_.log(LogLevel::kInfo, "Initializing ScannerEngine with ", workerCount, " workers.");

        for (std::size_t i = 0; i < workerCount; ++i)
        {
            workers_.emplace_back([this, i] { workerLoop(i); });  // All workers share ONE queue
        }
    }

    void submit(const ScanCommand &cmd)
    {
        if (shuttingDown_.load()) throw std::runtime_error("Engine is shutting down");
        queue_.push(cmd);  // ALL scan commands go to the SAME queue regardless of tenant type
    }

    // ...
private:
    BlockingQueue<ScanCommand>                  queue_;  // SINGLE shared queue for ALL tenants
    std::vector<std::thread>                    workers_;
    // ...
};
```

